" {TEXT -1 3 "6. " }{TEXT 267 33 "Fundamental Theorem of Arithmetic" }
{TEXT -1 148 ".  The Fundamental Theorem of Arithmetic states that eve
ry integer can be factored in a unique way into a product of powers of
 primes.  For example:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "84 = " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "``(2)^2*``(3)*``(7);" "6#*(-%!
G6#\"\"#F'-F%6#\"\"$\"\"\"-F%6#\"\"(F+" }{TEXT -1 4 " ;  " }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 9 "28490 =  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "``(2)*``(5)*``(7)*``(11)
*``(37);" "6#*,-%!G6#\"\"#\"\"\"-F%6#\"\"&F(-F%6#\"\"(F(-F%6#\"#6F(-F%
6#\"#PF(" }{TEXT -1 4 " ;  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 21 "5813258142
483000  =  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "``(2)^3*``(3)^4*``(5)^3*``(11)^2*``(23)^3
*``(29)*``(41)^2;" "6#*0-%!G6#\"\"#\"\"$-F%6#F(\"\"%-F%6#\"\"&F(-F%6#
\"#6F'-F%6#\"#BF(-F%6#\"#H\"\"\"-F%6#\"#TF'" }{TEXT -1 4 " .  " }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 17 "It is cal
led the " }{TEXT 270 11 "Fundamental" }{TEXT -1 217 " Theorem of Arith
metic because of the role it plays in both simple and deep results in \+
algebra and number theory.  There are numerous and important facts whi
ch follow because of  the Fundamental Theorem of Arithmetic." }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 10 "          " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 111 "Use
 paper and pencil to factor the following integers into their prime de
compositions:  340340, 38*865, 10!.   " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 266 19 "Answers:   340340 =" }{XPPEDIT 287 
0 "``(2)^2*``(5)*``(7)*``(11)*``(13)*``(17);" "6#*.-%!G6#\"\"#F'-F%6#
\"\"&\"\"\"-F%6#\"\"(F+-F%6#\"#6F+-F%6#\"#8F+-F%6#\"#<F+" }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 19 "                   " }{TEXT 288 9 "38*865 = " }
{XPPEDIT 289 0 "``(2)*``(5)*``(19)*``(173);" "6#**-%!G6#\"\"#\"\"\"-F%
6#\"\"&F(-F%6#\"#>F(-F%6#\"$t\"F(" }}{PARA 257 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 22 "  \+
                10!=" }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "``(2)^8*``(3)^4*``(5)^2*``(7);" 
"6#**-%!G6#\"\"#\"\")-F%6#\"\"$\"\"%-F%6#\"\"&F'-F%6#\"\"(\"\"\"" }}
