{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 384 "7.  Greatest Common Divisors and Least C
ommon Multiple (and the Fundamental Theorem of Arithmetic).  Maple can
 compute for a pair of integers (a,b) both the greatest common divisor
 of  (a,b) and the least common multiple of (a,b) easily.  The command
s for doing so are gcd(a,b) and lcm(a,b), respectively.  For each of t
he following pairs (a,b) find both the gcd(a,b) and the lcm(a,b)" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 105 "a.  74,1
48           b.  201, 1001         c.  202, 1002     d.  2432902008176
640000,41758540970065920000" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "gcd(74,148);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#\"#u" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "lcm(
74,148);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#\"$[\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 
"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "gcd(202,1002);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#\"\"#" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "lcm
(202,1002);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#\"'-75" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 46 "gcd(2432902008176640000,41758540970
065920000);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#\"1++ofV?Kv" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 46 "lcm(2432902008176640000,41758540970
065920000);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#\"8++;#HJLt3!)[8" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 74 "For the pair of numbers 144 and 84 execut
